</summary><content type="html">&lt;div class="section" id="introduction"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This document includes an external Python script to test syntax highlighting in Pelican.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="included-python-code"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Included Python Code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below is the content of &lt;cite&gt;example_code.py&lt;/cite&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code python literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# example_code.py&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;

&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sd"&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;
    Simple greeting function.
    &amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="sa"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;quot;Hello, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;!&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;

&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Calling the function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;quot;World&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="conclusion"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The code block above, included from an external file, should be syntax-highlighted if Pygments and Pelican are configured correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content><category term="Programming"></category><category term="python"></category><category term="code"></category><category term="external"></category></entry><entry><title>Python Code Example</title><link href="/2023/python-code-example.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2023-11-18T00:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2023-11-18T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>Dr Saad Laouadi</name></author><id>tag:None,2023-11-18:/2023/python-code-example.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p class="first last"&gt;A simple Python code example to test Pygments syntax highlighting.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary><content type="html">&lt;div class="section" id="introduction"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a test document to check whether Pygments is correctly highlighting Python code in your Pelican setup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="sample-python-code"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Sample Python Code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple Python function:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="w"&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sd"&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="sd"&gt;    Simple greeting function.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="sd"&gt;    &amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="sa"&gt;f&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;quot;Hello, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="si"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;!&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Calling the function&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="nb"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;greet&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s2"&gt;&amp;quot;World&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="conclusion"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The code block above should be syntax-highlighted if Pygments is configured correctly in your Pelican site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</content><category term="Programming"></category><category term="python"></category><category term="code"></category><category term="test"></category></entry><entry><title>Introduction to C++ Programming</title><link href="/2023/intro-to-cpp.html" rel="alternate"></link><published>2023-11-17T10:00:00+01:00</published><updated>2023-11-17T10:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>Dr Saad Laouadi</name></author><id>tag:None,2023-11-17:/2023/intro-to-cpp.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;p class="first last"&gt;A brief introduction to C++ programming with a simple example.&lt;/p&gt;
</summary><content type="html">&lt;div class="section" id="getting-started-with-c"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Getting Started with C++&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C++ is a widely-used programming language that offers a blend of high-level and low-level
features. In this post, we'll go through a basic &amp;quot;Hello, World!&amp;quot; program in C++.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="why-learn-c"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Why Learn C++?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C++ is known for its:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Performance&lt;/strong&gt;: It's incredibly efficient and is used in systems where resources are
limited or high performance is needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Control&lt;/strong&gt;: C++ gives programmers more control over system resources and memory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Object-Oriented Features&lt;/strong&gt;: C++ supports object-oriented programming, making it a
great choice for large-scale applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="hello-world-in-c"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Hello, World! in C++&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple C++ program that prints &amp;quot;Hello, World!&amp;quot; to the console:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code c++ literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="cp"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cpf"&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="cp"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="kt"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;std&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cout&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;Hello, World!&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;std&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;endl&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This program includes the &lt;cite&gt;&amp;lt;iostream&amp;gt;&lt;/cite&gt; library, which is used for input and output
operations. The &lt;cite&gt;main&lt;/cite&gt; function is the entry point of a C++ program. The line &lt;cite&gt;std::cout
&amp;lt;&amp;lt; &amp;quot;Hello, World!&amp;quot; &amp;lt;&amp;lt; std::endl;&lt;/cite&gt; prints the text to the console.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="conclusion"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;C++ is a powerful language for developing software that requires high performance and
resource management. This simple program is just the beginning of what you can do with
C++.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy coding!&lt;/p&gt;
